# psql backslash-command parity matrix.
#
# Each block: optional `skipif <engine>` directives, the command, `----`, and
# a golden block (each line prefixed `> `) captured once from real Postgres
# and committed. The harness diffs the configured engine's output against the
# golden; no live Postgres is needed at test time.
#   {schema}/{schema2} -> the per-run seeded schema names.
#   <NL>               -> a newline (for multi-step commands fed via stdin).
# Every command listed by psql's `\?` MUST appear here (active or skipif'd);
# the harness enforces that. See README.md for block syntax and how to
# refresh goldens via `run.py --update`.
#
# ---- client-side (server-independent; parity is trivially true) ----
\echo parity-marker
----
> parity-marker

\qecho parity-marker
----
> parity-marker

\warn parity-marker
----
> parity-marker

