# skip-line 1 (centered title -- leading spaces depend on total table
# width). skip-row drops rows whose value or presence is environment-
# dependent:
#   Host          -- 127.0.0.1 (dev) vs container hostname (CI)
#   Server Port   -- 5433 (dev) vs 5432/7777 (CI)
#   Backend PID   -- random per connection
#   GSSAPI / SSL  -- present only when libpq was built with krb5 / openssl
#   (N rows)      -- the count drifts when GSSAPI/SSL rows come and go
# Block-local cell-pad + border-dash collapse is applied automatically.
skipif postgres
skip-line: 1
skip-row: ^\| (Host|Server Port|Backend PID|GSSAPI Authenticated|SSL Connection)
skip-row: ^\(\d+ rows?\)$
\conninfo
----
>        Connection Information
> +----------------------+------------+
> |      Parameter       |   Value    |
> +----------------------+------------+
> | Database             | postgres   |
> | Client User          | postgres   |
> | Host                 | 127.0.0.1  |
> | Server Port          | 5433       |
> | Options              |            |
> | Protocol Version     | 3.0        |
> | Password Used        | false      |
> | GSSAPI Authenticated | false      |
> | Backend PID          | OID |
> | SSL Connection       | false      |
> | Superuser            | on         |
> | Hot Standby          | off        |
> +----------------------+------------+
> (12 rows)

