# Scoped to schemas with our run-id suffix (psqlh_<suffix>, psqlh2_<suffix>)
# so prior drivers' residual schemas in shared CI state don't pollute the
# diff. `public` (owner divergence vs PG18) and other test schemas are
# excluded by the pattern.
\dn psqlh*_{suffix}
----
>       List of schemas
> +---------------+----------+
> |     Name      |  Owner   |
> +---------------+----------+
> | SCHEMA2 | postgres |
> | SCHEMA  | postgres |
> +---------------+----------+
> (2 rows)

# ---- skips: body/definition text requires PG ruleutils-style pretty-printer ----
# PG reformats view/function bodies (multi-line indent, '::text' literal casts,
# LANGUAGE clauses); serened returns the raw stored CREATE statement / DuckDB
# CREATE FUNCTION form, so the bodies legitimately differ.
# view body: PG ruleutils-rendered vs serened's raw CREATE statement
\sv
----
> view name is required

# function body: DuckDB CREATE FUNCTION form vs PG ruleutils rendering
\sf
----
> function name is required

